# Email Deliverability Info
msgid "plugins.generic.mailSettings.deliverability.title"
msgstr "Email Deliverability Recommendations"

msgid "plugins.generic.mailSettings.deliverability.intro"
msgstr "To ensure emails reach recipients and avoid spam folders, ask your server administrator or hosting provider to configure the following DNS records for your domain:"

msgid "plugins.generic.mailSettings.deliverability.spf"
msgstr "Authorizes your SMTP server to send emails on behalf of your domain. Without SPF, receiving servers may reject or flag your emails."

msgid "plugins.generic.mailSettings.deliverability.dkim"
msgstr "Adds a digital signature to outgoing emails, proving they were not altered in transit. Significantly improves inbox delivery rates."

msgid "plugins.generic.mailSettings.deliverability.dmarc"
msgstr "Tells receiving servers how to handle emails that fail SPF/DKIM checks. Protects your domain from spoofing and phishing."

msgid "plugins.generic.mailSettings.deliverability.note"
msgstr "These settings are configured at the DNS level by your domain/hosting provider, not within OJS. If you use a service like Gmail or Yandex for SMTP, their documentation provides the required DNS records. Contact your server administrator for assistance."

